reviews.text: I love cooking but there times - momma needs a night off!!! Well feeding my starving family is not an option I know that Joe‚Äôs Meat Market always has my back!  Whether it‚Äôs subs for a concert, family style meals, breakfast sandwiches, pizza, the list goes on.  I‚Äôve been a customer since I moved into SBB 23 years ago.  When I was pregnant and could not shop for meat - Joe had me covered and cut everything to my liking and request.  I appreciate a good butcher and helps save me time, money, and my sanity having my meats cut accordingly to my requests.  We order meats often for bulk or batch cooking which goes great for my freezer meals!  Hands down Joe‚Äôs is my go-to for everything especially when I do not want to cook!!!

On a rather warm day, I stopped in to get a quick bite for the road. The Italian sandwich hit the spot just perfectly. Not overdone or overpowering with the toppings, and the meat portion was nicely substantive. The prices were quite reasonable, and I found the service to be friendly and engaging. It was a pleasure coming here.

Pizzeria in the front, deli in the back, street parking. Got the $7 cheese steak special. It was a good size for the price. The steak was underseasoned and a little dry, while the bread was nice and crusty on the outside while soft and fluffy on the inside. I noticed the 2 pizza slices and a can of soda for $5 special - that's value!

Visited this DDD spot and was impressed with the place.  The staff was jovial and conversational which made for a pleasant meal.  The food was delish, portions plentiful, and prices reasonable - an all around good experience.

Saw this place on Triple D and just had to check it out. It was worth the minor detour and I would definitely go again. They don‚Äôt skimp on anything and like the kid who was featured on the show said ‚Äúwe aim to feed‚Äù. High quality meats, cheeses and breads. Highlights are definitely the antipasto bread, the sloppy Joe and the Italian. Looking forward to finding a way to get back here soon.

detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôve been following Joe‚Äôs on Facebook for a while - recommendation from my uncle who orders regularly.  They have fantastic weekly specials.  I finally decided to order their Pizza Bread special one night and WOW.  Came with four, generously stuffed pizza breads - chicken parm, pepperoni, sausage and cheesesteak - and fed three adults for a few meals.  Just ordered their Friday pizza special - and that deal cannot be beat.  Great pizza at an amazing price.  Both times, the staff was accommodating and friendly - and the food was incredible - both in taste and price.  Highly recommend.

detailedReviews.text:
I would give 0 stars to this place just for the simple fact of who owns it!!!!
Do not, I repeat do not book any event at Giovanni‚Äôs in SBB. My bridal shower was booked here in March. On Thursday we found out that JOE (the owner of joes meat market) double booked the day for another event (his friend the mayors 70th birthday party). There was no apologies, no accommodations. Told us we couldn‚Äôt have my bridal shower there anymore, along with DISGUSTING behavior from both Joe and Giovanni. After endlessly supporting Joe and his family, they will push you to the curb with NO apologies. Can you imagine 3 weeks out and no place to hold the shower!!!!!! If you ever try to do an event there, beware!!!!!! I would appreciate if all would use this info and think twice before ever supporting this family after what they did to myself and my family.

detailedReviews.author: Vanessa
detailedReviews.text:
I have been a loyal customer of this establishment for over four years, but unfortunately, yesterday‚Äôs experience will be my last. Approximately 2‚Äì3 weeks ago, I called to inquire about pricing for three large plain pizzas. I spoke directly with Joe, the owner, who personally quoted me a specific price for the order.

I placed the order the yesterday morning, requesting the pizzas be ready by 10:30 AM. Upon arriving, I attempted to speak to the staff at the pizza counter‚Äîspecifically, a Hispanic gentleman about the price Joe had given me. Rather than assisting me, he responded with clear attitude, handed me the receipt, and dismissively said, ‚ÄúGo over there‚Äù I was taken aback by the unnecessary rudeness.

When I went to the checkout area, I explained the same situation again. Instead of offering any assistance or clarification, the staff member responded with, ‚ÄúNext time make sure you tell me over the phone,‚Äù in a similarly dismissive tone. Frankly, I fail to see the relevance of whether I confirm pricing over the phone or in person‚Äîespecially when the owner himself provided the quote.

The lack of professionalism and courtesy I encountered was disappointing and unacceptable. After years of supporting this business, I will no longer be spending my money here. Customer loyalty and respect should go both ways.

detailedReviews.author: Cindy Masters
detailedReviews.text: I would have given them a four-star review but I was sent a text for a special, 8.99 for a large plain pizza. I normally like their pizza but I wish I had opened the box before leaving. Worst pizza ever. In my opinion the pizza was pre- made and reheated. It was dry, overcooked and certainly not a large. If you're going to have a special then make it special. We're not stupid, it should have been the same quality as a full priced pizza. That was a waste of money and we couldn't eat it. I wanted to add mushrooms and pay extra for the topping. Suddenly the pizza went from$8.99 to $15.00- $6.00 extra dollars for mushrooms? Needless to say I did not get the mushrooms for $6.00 extra! I'll drive the extra 10 minutes and go to Ferrara's on Lincoln Blvd. I rated it a two only because they do have fairly good cheeseburgers. I started ordering my burgers medium well because if I ordered them medium they were more rare than medium. No more pizza from Joe's.

detailedReviews.author: Donna Locke
detailedReviews.text:
We have used their catering services at least 5 times. From a graduate party, wedding reception, bridal shower and several surprise parties The food has always been perfectly  delicious!
We have picked up and had many deliveries . Food is hot and always on time with everything you forgot you needed!
The veterans in Dunellen have also been using their services for many occasions. Both the American Legion the Veterans of Foreign War. They have treated us with the most respect. I highly recommend them for every occasion. They are fabulous and it makes your occasion easy and enjoyable. Authentic meals, great prices and more time to spend with the ones you wanted to be with. Definitely a easy and delicious experience and my personal go place for years. üòã

detailedReviews.author: Mauricio Zecca
detailedReviews.text:
One of Our Go-To Spots!

At Aura Home Exteriors, we‚Äôre always on the move working jobs around town‚Äîand whenever we‚Äôre nearby, Joe‚Äôs Meat Market is one of our go-to spots. The sandwiches are consistently excellent‚Äîfresh, flavorful, and made with quality ingredients.

The staff is always friendly and welcoming, which makes grabbing lunch here a real pleasure. Prices are great, especially for the quality and service you get. Joe‚Äôs hits the mark every time. Highly recommended if you‚Äôre in the area!
